[medium] src/views/system-security-plans/partials/StatementByComponent.vue:45 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library)
The inline editor stores localComponent as the exact props.byComponent object, and the edit controls bind to localComponent.description/status. Because nested prop objects are mutated by reference, typing in edit mode changes the parent controlImplementation tree before Save; clicking Cancel only flips editing off, leaving the unsaved description/status visible and eligible for later saves even though no PUT succeeded.
Suggested fix: Create an isolated draft when entering edit mode, for example structuredClone(props.byComponent) or a local clone helper, bind the form to that draft, emit a normalized clone on Save, and discard/reinitialize the draft on Cancel or when props.byComponent changes.
Guidance: In src/views/system-security-plans/partials/StatementByComponent.vue, localComponent is currently initialized as ref<ByComponent>(props.byComponent) and reset in watchEffect to the same prop object. That means v-model='localComponent.description' and the statusState/statusRemarks computed setters mutate props.byComponent by reference before Save. Replace this with an isolated edit draft. Add a small clone helper in this file, for example function cloneByComponent(value: ByComponent): ByComponent { return structuredClone(value); } if the test/runtime supports structuredClone, otherwise JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(value)) is acceptable for this OSCAL data. Initialize localComponent from cloneByComponent(props.byComponent), and replace watchEffect with a watch on () => props.byComponent that assigns a fresh clone when the prop changes; do not overwrite the draft while editing unless the prop object actually changes from the parent after a save/refetch. Change the BurgerMenu Edit command to reset localComponent.value = cloneByComponent(props.byComponent) before setEditing(true). Change cancel() to reset localComponent.value = cloneByComponent(props.byComponent) and then setEditing(false). Keep save() emitting normalizeByComponentImplementationStatus(cloneByComponent(localComponent.value)) so the parent receives a normalized copy, not the mutable draft object, then setEditing(false). deleteStatement() should keep emitting props.byComponent or a clone of it, not a possibly dirty canceled draft. Add a unit test in src/views/system-security-plans/partials/__tests__/StatementByComponent.spec.ts that mounts with a byComponent object, enters edit mode, changes the description and implementation status/remarks, clicks Cancel, and asserts the original byComponent prop object is unchanged and no save was emitted. Avoid changing emitted event names, SSP endpoints, risk widget behavior, or the parent store semantics.

